Rating: 0
To keep any cheesecake from cracking cook it in a water bath. Be sure to cover the bottom of your sprinform with foil to keep the water out. Use hot watete for the bath and fill it up about halfway on your springform. After the cake is cooked, turn off you stove and leave the cake in the water bath for one hour and then put it in the fridge. Cheesecakes are not a true "cake" but more of a custard due to the amount of eggs, thus the water bath.

