Rating: 4
I found this to be a very good cheesecake, a nice mix between a pumpkin pie and a traditional cheesecake. Has the flavor and even the texture a bit of pumpkin pie, but is dressed up in cheesecake clothes. I found the crust to be fantastic...the cookies plus pecans made me wonder why I hadn't thought of such a thing before. I cooked mine in a water bath and still had some cracks and a little darkness on top. I agree that the topping is not necessary for flavor, but it was good to have to cover up some of the ugliness on the top of the cake. You can halve the recipe of the topping, however...I threw most of mine away. The filling will be too much for your pan...simply pour the leftover into a pie pan and have a little extra. A question for South Haven - if you noticed you had too much filling, why did you keep pouring? Is your review for the quality of the finished product or for the fact that it overflowed on you?

